HEADWORD: Bordeaux mixture
<hw>Bor*deaux" mix"ture</hw>. <fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>A fungicidal
mixture composed of blue vitriol, lime, and water. The formula in common
use is: blue vitriol, 6 lbs.; lime, 4 lbs.; water, 35 -- 50
gallons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bordello</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Bordel</ent>⟦br⟧
